[14:47:39] [33mWARN[39m: [36mPUT /api/issues/61509b0f-82cc-4825-8e35-868873e7ecd4/documents/plan 409[39m [90m{"reqBody":{"title":null,"format":"markdown","body":"# Mi1k Application Plan\n\nTwo workstreams under this brief: (A) pre-built workflow plugins, (B) upstream sync + click-through updates.\n\n***\n\n## Part A: Workflow Plugins\n\n### Open Questions — Resolved\n\n| # | Question                     | Board Answer                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |\n| - | ---------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| 1 | MCP availability             | MCPs will always be connected on client instances. No graceful degradation needed — design for always-on MCP.                                                                                                                                  |\n| 2 | Plugin distribution          | Ship bundled with the app (not npm install-on-demand). They appear pre-loaded on the Workflows page.                                                                                                                                           |\n| 3 | Branding                     | Yes — workflows should carry Mi1k/Rindquip branding for client installs.                                                                                                                                                                       |\n| 4 | Scope of AI / human approval | Human approval stage required, configurable per workflow. Each workflow gets an `approvalMode` setting: `auto` (agent acts immediately), `staged` (agent drafts, human approves), or `notify-only` (agent logs, no action). Default: `staged`. |\n\n### The 4 Workflows (unchanged from prior plan)\n\n1. **Smart Inbox Commander** — email triage + auto-routing + draft responses\n2. **Weekly Business Pulse Report** — automated KPI collection + AI executive summary\n3. **Inbound Lead Qualification Pipeline** — webhook-triggered research + scoring + task routing\n4. **Document Intake & Processing** — auto-extract invoices/contracts/reports + classify + route\n\nAll leverage plugin tools, jobs, webhooks, MCPs, Brand Brain. All appear as installable cards on the Workflows page with Mi1k branding.\n\nEach plugin now includes the `approvalMode` config field. When set to `staged`, the agent creates a draft/proposal task and assigns it for human review before executing the action (sending email, creating external records, etc.).\n\nFull workflow details preserved from prior plan revision — see individual workflow sections below.\n\n***\n\n## Part B: Upstream Sync + Click-Through Updates\n\n### Current State\n\n* **Mi1k fork**: 11 custom commits ahead of upstream\n* **Upstream**: 2,185 commits ahead of Mi1k (327 files changed, 150k+ insertions)\n* **Upstream remote**: already configured (`upstream` → [`https://github.com/paperclipai/paperclip.git`)](https://github.com/paperclipai/paperclip.git\))\n* **Merge risk**: Low — Mi1k customizations are localized. No conflicts in dry-run. But upstream removed some of our custom pages (BrandBrain.tsx, Documents.tsx, Workflows.tsx, MilkDocs.tsx) which need preservation.\n\n### Key Upstream Features We're Missing\n\n* Issue workflow refinements and signoff staging\n* Routine defaults and runtime overrides\n* Parent-child issue nesting in inbox\n* Execution workspace issues tab\n* Adapter Manager UI (new component)\n* Issue Chat UX Lab (experimental)\n* Keyboard shortcuts cheatsheet\n* Enhanced feedback/approval systems\n* Significant test coverage expansion\n\n### Upstream Sync Strategy\n\n**Principle**: Pull upstream features, don't recreate them. Preserve Mi1k-specific customizations.\n\n**Step 1 — Rebase prep (low risk)**\n\n1. Tag current state: `git tag mi1k-v0.3.2-pre-sync`\n2. Create sync branch: `git checkout -b upstream-sync-v0.4`\n3. Fetch latest upstream: `git fetch upstream`\n\n**Step 2 — Merge upstream into sync branch**\n\n1. `git merge upstream/main` on the sync branch\n2. Resolve conflicts — the main conflict areas will be:\n   * **Custom UI pages**: upstream deleted BrandBrain.tsx, Documents.tsx, Workflows.tsx, MilkDocs.tsx. We keep ours by restoring them from our branch and re-adding route entries.\n   * **Sidebar customization**: our \"Tasks\" rename and version display need re-application.\n   * **pnpm-lock.yaml**: regenerate with `pnpm install`.\n   * **Middleware**: our custom middleware (session rotator, wiki seeder, context injector, reporter, extractor, update-checker) lives in `middleware/` which upstream doesn't touch — clean merge.\n   * **Custom adapters**: our `claude-api`, `openrouter`, `openai-compatible` adapters in `server/src/adapters/` may need interface updates if upstream changed the adapter contract.\n3. Run full build: `pnpm build` — fix any TypeScript errors from interface changes.\n4. Run DB migration check: compare our Drizzle schema with upstream's — apply any new migrations.\n\n**Step 3 — Validate**\n\n1. Start local instance, verify all custom pages load.\n2. Verify all upstream features work (inbox nesting, adapter manager, keyboard shortcuts).\n3. Run existing test suite.\n4. Confirm middleware daemon starts and all 6 jobs run.\n5. Confirm hub reporting still works.\n\n**Step 4 — Merge to main**\n\n1. PR from `upstream-sync-v0.4` → `main`\n2. Tag `mi1k-v0.4.0`\n3. Build new portable tarball\n\n**Ongoing sync cadence**: Monthly upstream fetch + merge. Keep customizations in clearly separated files/directories to minimize conflict surface.\n\n### Click-Through Update System\n\n**Current state**: `update-checker.ts` does `git fetch` and compares local HEAD vs `origin/main`. Returns `updateAvailable` boolean. Reporter sends this flag to hub. No UI, no API for triggering updates.\n\n**Target state**: Client sees \"Update available\" banner in the UI, clicks to update, app applies update and restarts.\n\n**Implementation plan:**\n\n#### 1. Backend — System Update API\n\nNew endpoint: `GET /api/system/update-status`\n\n* Returns: `{ updateAvailable: boolean, currentVersion: string, latestVersion: string, commitsBehind: number, releaseNotes: string | null }`\n* Sources data from existing `update-checker.ts`\n\nNew endpoint: `POST /api/system/update`\n\n* Auth: board-level only (not agents)\n* Executes update sequence:\n  1. `git fetch origin`\n  2. `git stash` (preserve local data changes if any)\n  3. `git merge origin/main --ff-only` (fast-forward only — refuse if conflicts)\n  4. `pnpm install && pnpm build`\n  5. Run any new DB migrations\n  6. Restart services via launchd/Task Scheduler\n* Returns: `{ status: 'updating' | 'failed', message: string }`\n* Streams progress via WebSocket event `system:update-progress`\n\nNew endpoint: `POST /api/system/update/rollback`\n\n* Reverts to the tagged pre-update commit if update failed\n* Uses the backup mechanism already in `mi1k-update.sh`\n\n#### 2. Frontend — Update Banner Component\n\nNew component: `UpdateBanner.tsx`\n\n* Polls `GET /api/system/update-status` on app load (cached, refreshed every hour)\n* Displays persistent banner when update available: \"Mi1k v0.4.0 available — \[Update Now]\"\n* Click triggers confirmation modal with release notes\n* On confirm, POST to `/api/system/update`, show progress overlay\n* On completion, prompt page reload\n\n#### 3. Distribution Pipeline\n\nFor git-based installs (current model):\n\n* Click-through update \= `git pull origin main` + rebuild + restart\n* Works today, just needs the UI trigger\n\nFor portable tarball installs:\n\n* Update API downloads new tarball from a release URL, extracts, swaps binaries, restarts\n* Requires a release server (could be GitHub Releases or the hub)\n* `mi1k-update.sh` already handles tarball-based updates with rollback — just needs an API trigger\n\n#### 4. Safety Rails\n\n* **Pre-update DB backup**: automatic snapshot before any update\n* **Fast-forward only**: refuse merge if conflicts exist (user must resolve manually or wait for clean release)\n* **Rollback**: one-click revert to previous version + DB restore\n* **Staged rollout**: hub can flag specific versions as stable/beta, client chooses update track\n* **No data loss**: `paperclip-data/` directory is never touched by updates (gitignored)\n\n***\n\n## Sequencing\n\n| Phase | Work                                           | Depends On                                 |\n| ----- | ---------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |\n| 1     | Upstream sync (merge 2,185 commits)            | Nothing — can start now                    |\n| 2     | Click-through update backend + frontend        | Phase 1 (need clean merged codebase)       |\n| 3     | Workflow plugin scaffold + Inbox Commander     | Phase 1 (need upstream plugin SDK updates) |\n| 4     | Remaining 3 workflow plugins                   | Phase 3                                    |\n| 5     | Build portable tarball v0.4.0 for distribution | Phases 1-3                                 |\n\n***\n\n## Open Questions for Board\n\n1. **Release server for tarball updates**: Should we use GitHub Releases, the hub, or a separate CDN for hosting update tarballs?\n2. **Update track**: Should clients be able to choose stable vs beta update channels?\n3. **Upstream sync frequency**: Monthly merge recommended — acceptable cadence?","baseRevisionId":"46a0c27a-3c9d-4fa6-a0e7-455951049426"},"routePath":"/issues/:id/documents/:key"}[39m
